# ACABOS First Steps

This file explains how to use the supported tooling installed on this system.

## Hardware Posture

- GPU Vendor: `__ACAB_GPU_VENDOR__`
- GPU Support Tier: `__ACAB_GPU_TIER__`
- GPU Runtime Target: `__ACAB_GPU_RUNTIME__`

## Runtime Readiness

First-boot provisioning writes:

- `/etc/acabos/runtime-readiness.tsv`
- `/etc/acabos/runtime-readiness.log`

Review them first:

```bash
sudo cat /etc/acabos/runtime-readiness.tsv
sudo less /etc/acabos/runtime-readiness.log
```

## Ollama

Check status:

```bash
systemctl status ollama.service --no-pager
```

Start or enable if needed:

```bash
sudo systemctl start ollama.service
sudo systemctl enable ollama.service
```

## mistral.rs

Profiles live in:

```bash
/etc/acabos/inference/
```

An example profile was installed at:

```bash
/etc/acabos/inference/example.env
```

Start a profile with:

```bash
sudo systemctl start acab-inference@<profile>.service
sudo systemctl status acab-inference@<profile>.service --no-pager
```

Or use the helper:

```bash
model-manager serve <profile>
```

## Jupyter

Jupyter is local-only and disabled by default.

Generated token:

```text
__ACAB_JUPYTER_TOKEN__
```

Enable and start:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable acab-jupyter.service
sudo systemctl start acab-jupyter.service
```

Access URL:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8888
```

Notebook root:

```text
/home/__ACAB_USERNAME__/workspace/notebooks
```

## Containerized Services

Check retained services:

```bash
ai-stack status
```

Start them all:

```bash
sudo ai-stack up
```

Or individually:

```bash
sudo systemctl start qdrant.service
sudo systemctl start localai.service
sudo systemctl start comfyui.service
```

Useful endpoints:

- Qdrant: `http://localhost:6333`
- LocalAI: `http://localhost:8081`
- ComfyUI: `http://localhost:8188`

## Logs

```bash
journalctl -u ollama.service -f
journalctl -u qdrant.service -f
journalctl -u localai.service -f
journalctl -u comfyui.service -f
journalctl -u acab-jupyter.service -f
```
